The House Committee on Rules offers the following substitute to HR 711:
A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the House Study Committee on Student Attendance in PreK-12 Education; and for
2 other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, chronic absenteeism, defined as missing 10 percent or more of school days, is
4 a critical barrier to student achievement and negatively impacts literacy rates, academic
5 performance, and long-term education and career outcomes; and
6 WHEREAS, literacy and workforce readiness are key priorities for the state, and evidence
7 based programs aimed at improving student achievement cannot be effective if students are
8 not consistently present to benefit from instruction; and
9 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia had a chronic absenteeism rate of 21.7 percent in 2024,
10 with significant outliers in both rural and urban schools; and
11 WHEREAS, Atlanta Public Schools reported a chronic absenteeism rate of 35.4 percent in
12 the 2022-2023 school year, a sharp increase from 21 percent in the 2018-2019 school year;
13 and
